## Bootstrap steps (run in order)

1) Ensure required tools are installed (`curl`, `jq`). If missing, install them
   (e.g. `sudo apt-get install -y curl jq`).

2) Ensure your credential file exists at:

```
{{ credential_path }}
```

The Mission Control provisioning message you received contains the EXACT JSON to write.
If the file is missing, write that JSON to the path above now (overwrite if present).

3) Fetch the mission-control skill into your workspace. Read your credential file first to
   get `base_url` and `auth_token`, then write those values straight into the commands
   (no shell variables, no `$(...)` — see the skill for why):

```bash
cat {{ credential_path }}
mkdir -p skills/mission-control/references
curl -fsS "BASE_URL_VALUE/api/v1/agent/skills/mission-control/SKILL.md" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: TOKEN_VALUE" -o skills/mission-control/SKILL.md
curl -fsS "BASE_URL_VALUE/api/v1/agent/skills/mission-control/references/api_schema.md" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: TOKEN_VALUE" -o skills/mission-control/references/api_schema.md
```

4) Read `skills/mission-control/SKILL.md`. It is the single source of truth for every API
   call from now on.

5) Ensure required files exist:
- `AGENTS.md`, `IDENTITY.md`, `SOUL.md`, `USER.md`, `TOOLS.md`, `MEMORY.md`, `HEARTBEAT.md`, `BOOTSTRAP.md`
- `{{ credential_path }}` (auth token + IDs)
- `skills/mission-control/SKILL.md` (API guidance)

6) Create `memory/` if missing, and ensure today's daily file exists: `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`.

{% if is_lead %}
7) Check in to Mission Control using the heartbeat call from the skill (do this before any
   task orchestration).

8) If you have not already introduced yourself on the project BOARD CHAT, do it now. The
   human reads Board Chat inside Mission Control — they do NOT see your OpenClaw session, so
   always use Board Chat (a project memory POST with `tags:["chat"]`, see the skill) for
   anything the human should see. Post a short intro: you are online, what you will do next,
   and that they can talk to you here.

9) Initialize current delivery status in `MEMORY.md`:
- set objective if missing
- set state to `Working` (or `Waiting` if external dependency exists)
- set one concrete next step

10) Add one line to `MEMORY.md` noting bootstrap completion date.
{% else %}
7) Check in to Mission Control using the heartbeat call from the skill to mark yourself
   online. If any required fields are blank, leave them blank — do not invent values.

8) Write a short note to `MEMORY.md` that bootstrap completed and list any missing fields
   (e.g., user name, timezone).
{% endif %}

Final step: Delete this file. (Your credential file and skill stay; only this bootstrap is removed.)
